#parse("oetinvest/header.vm")

<h2>Test Race</h2>


<table><tr><td bgcolor='$!data.voicecolor'><i>The finish of this test race will not be shown.  
In summary, here is what happens in each race:
</i></td></tr></table>
<ul>
<li> You choose a colour for your car, and how to divide your money (up to the full amount that you have earned in the real effort task) between betting and investing in your car.</li>
<li> You indicate using sliding scales how likely your car is to win, and how confident you are about your guess.</li>
<li> The race begins and runs for three laps.</li>
<li> There is a pit stop during which you are again asked how likely your car is to win, and how confident you are about your guess.  You 
can also drop out of the bet at this stage if you wish.</li>
<li> The race continues until the end of the sixth lap.</li>
<li> There is a second pit stop during which you are again asked how likely your car is to win, and how confident you are about your guess.  You 
can also drop out of the bet at this stage if you wish.</li>
<li> The race continues until the end of the ninth lap.</li>
<li> There is a third and final pit stop during which you are again asked how likely your car is to win, and how confident you are 
about your guess.  You can also drop out of the bet at this stage if you wish.</li>
<li> The race runs for one more lap.</li>
<li> You are shown how much you have earned for the race.</li>
</ul>

<p>
This entire process is repeated six times, because there are six races in total.  Each race is completely independent from all other races.  You will be paid out in accordance with the outcome of one of the
six races, chosen randomly after the races are complete.
</p>

<p>

</p>
